videos.description: RB Kennedy McKoy gets great blocking for an easy 5-yard touchdown, putting West Virginia up early at 7-0.
videos.headline: McKoy walks into end zone for early lead

videos.description: Oklahoma State WR Tylan Wallace extends to his left to grab a 7-yard touchdown, tying it at 7.
videos.headline: Wallace reaches out for TD to tie game

videos.description: Gary Jennings Jr. jukes a defender in the open field, then runs to the end zone to put West Virginia back on top.
videos.headline: Jennings fools defender for TD

videos.description: QB Will Grier throws a pass into a very small window to David Sills V for the touchdown.
videos.headline: Grier tosses dime for TD

videos.description: TE Logan Carter drags a defender with him into the end zone on his first career catch to bring Oklahoma State within one score.
videos.headline: Cowboys TE drags defender for TD on 1st career catch

videos.description: Kennedy McKoy finds open field on a 30-yard touchdown run, his second of the game, putting him over 100 rushing yards.
videos.headline: McKoy's 2nd TD puts him over 100 rushing yards

videos.description: The Mountaineers built a 31-14 halftime lead on Oklahoma State thanks to some big plays by RB Kennedy McKoy.

videos.headline: West Virginia pours on offense in first half

videos.description: Oklahoma State QB Tyler Cornelius throws a back-door fade to Tyron Johnson to trim West Virginia's lead to 34-31.
videos.headline: Cornelius connects on fade to trim deficit

videos.description: After a 4th-down pass interference call in the end zone, Will Grier capitalizes with a 6-yard touchdown run.
videos.headline: Grier capitalizes on 4th-down PI with TD

videos.description: QB Taylor Cornelius spins into the end zone to trim the Cowboys' deficit  to 41-38 with under 5 minutes left.
videos.headline: Cornelius spins around defender for TD

videos.description: Tylan Wallace fights into the end zone to give the Cowboys their first lead of the game with under one minute remaining.
videos.headline: Oklahoma State gets their 1st lead of the game in final minute

videos.description: Will Grier's pass is knocked away on the final play of the game to seal Oklahoma State's 45-41 upset over No. 9 West Virginia.
videos.headline: West Virginia can't capitalize in final seconds, falls to Oklahoma State

videos.description: Taylor Cornelius puts up five touchdowns on 338 yards in Oklahoma State's wild upset over West Virginia 45-41.
